Pencil and watercolor drawing for "Thoughts About People,"
                                from Sketches By Boz,
                                watermarked

prose, biographical sketch of Shelley (in unknown hand),
                                    3 pp., undated; rosebud from Shelley's grave, Rome, 1859 spring;
                                    note signed by Shelley, 1816; miscellaneous papers

Autograph Letters: 26 (1776-1814) to various people, such as
                                Joseph Cradock, Madame Mara, Hester Ogle Sheridan, and Charles Ward;
                                2 ( 1803, 1816) letter about, one by Peter Moore

Indenture signed, with Wm. Siddons, 1799 November 21 for a
                                private box in the Theatre Royal, Drury Lane, 2 pp.,
                                1799

scopecontent.p:
The collector of these materials is unknown, and some items may have come
                            from different sources. The manuscripts are written in various hands,
                            though some in the collection are in the same hand.

Statement of fees paid to Exchequer officers; judges and court officials;
                            customs officers, auditors and receivers in the duchy of Lancaster;
                            surveyors of royal lands; musicians, physicians, apothecaries,
                            astronomers, cooks, stationers, printers, shipwrights, and other
                            employees of the Great Wardrobe; military officers in fortifications;
                            and keepers of royal palaces.
